properties.Name: WorkOrder
properties.Description:
An order to perform one or Work Activity(s) in conjunction with a Service Request.

Work Order Activities are activities that require additional personnel, planning, supporting material and effort.

A Service Request differs from a Work Order in that: a Work Order has the following characteristics that a Service Request does not:

- May require additional personnel with specific skills
- May require supporting consumables or inventory items
- May require one or more manual or technical work order activities
- May require one or more assets or property & equipment
- May involve work order activity costs that are charged to various related parties, organizations etc.

Columns.Name: WorkOrderId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Work Order.

Columns.Name: WorkOrderDescription
Columns.Description: A description of the Work Order.

Columns.Name: WorkOrderSubmittedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the Work Order was submitted to manufacturing.

Columns.Name: WorkOrderReceivedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the work order was received.

Columns.Name: WorkOrderScheduledTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the work order was scheduled.

Columns.Name: WorkOrderDispatchedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the work order was dispatched.

Columns.Name: WorkOrderCompletedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the Work Order was completed.

Columns.Name: WorkOrderClosedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the work order was closed.

Columns.Name: LocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Location.

Columns.Name: ServiceRequestId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Service Request.

Columns.Name: IssueId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Issue.

Columns.Name: WorkOrderTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Work Order Type.

Columns.Name: WorkOrderPriorityId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Work Order Priority.

Columns.Name: ResponsibilityCenterId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Responsibility Center.

Columns.Name: WorkOrderGlAccountNumber
Columns.Description: The GL Account Number assigned to a Work Order.
